  "exec_summary": "The European Securities and Markets Authority has declared that prediction markets will be subject to the binary options ban, with ESMA applying this regulation to firms such as Kalshi, a significant development in the EU's regulatory oversight of emerging financial products. In related news, Revolut is delisting USDT in Europe ahead of the Markets in Crypto-Assets regulation, highlighting the impact of MiCA on the crypto industry. Meanwhile, the European Insurance and Occupational Pensions Authority has launched a consultation on the review of insurance disclosures under the Taxonomy Disclosures Delegated Act, demonstrating ongoing regulatory activity in the EU. In Belgium, there are no notable developments this week, but firms such as Paytm have secured payment institution licenses in Luxembourg, indicating the ongoing expansion of fintech firms in the EU.",
